														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3570628">
									

<p>Cute as hell, and that final line sold me on an upvote.</p>
<p>It's narration comes across as a little more childish than its speech in the mainlist article, so it's voice feels a bit inconsistent between the two works, but it's not wildly different.</p>
<p>I would have preferred some interaction with the outside world/the 001, because it would have been interesting to see how 2785, whose purpose is to serve humans, tries to fulfill the needs of what's become of humanity; and also because this could have been any XK and worked just as well.</p>

							</div>

								
					
